# Markdown Cross-Reference Standards

## Description

This rule enforces proper cross-document linking standards in markdown files. All references to other documents or sections MUST use explicit markdown link syntax with relative paths. Referencing documents by name alone is prohibited.

**Primary Focus**: Proper link syntax and relative path usage

## Rule

**MANDATORY REQUIREMENTS:**

1. **Explicit Link Syntax**
   - MUST: Use markdown link syntax `[text](./path/to/file.md)`
   - PROHIBITED: Referencing documents by name alone ("See CONTRIBUTING.md")
   - PROHIBITED: Bare URLs without link text

2. **Relative Paths**
   - MUST: Use relative paths from current file location
   - Format: `./file.md` (same directory), `../file.md` (parent), `../../file.md` (grandparent)
   - MUST: Include file extension (`.md`)

3. **Anchor Links**
   - MUST: Use anchor syntax for section references `[text](./file.md#section-title)`
   - Format: Section titles in lowercase with dashes: `#my-section-title`
   - Spaces in section titles become dashes in anchor links

4. **Link Validation**
   - All referenced files MUST exist
   - All anchor links MUST point to existing sections
   - Broken links are validation failures

## Implementation

- Real-time link syntax validation
- Broken link detection during editing
- Auto-completion for file paths
- Anchor link suggestions based on existing headers

## Benefits

1. **Navigate Reliability**: Links work correctly in all markdown viewers
2. **Refactoring Safety**: IDEs can update links when files move
3. **Validation**: Broken links can be detected automatically
4. **Clarity**: Explicit links show relationship between documents

## Examples

### ✅ Correct Cross-References

` ``markdown
See the [Setup section](./CONTRIBUTING.md#setup) for installation instructions.

For more details, refer to the [API documentation](./docs/api-reference.md).

Check the [configuration guide](../config/settings.md#database-configuration).
` ``

### ❌ Incorrect Cross-References

` ``markdown
❌ See the "Setup" section in the contribution guide.
   (No explicit link)

❌ Refer to CONTRIBUTING.md for more details.
   (Document name without link syntax)

❌ See [this document](CONTRIBUTING.md).
   (Missing ./ for relative path)

❌ Check the setup documentation.
   (Vague reference, no link)
` ``

### Anchor Link Examples

` ``markdown
✅ CORRECT:
# My Section Title

[Link to section](#my-section-title)
[Link in other file](./other.md#my-section-title)

❌ INCORRECT:
[Link with spaces](#My Section Title)  ❌ Spaces not converted to dashes
[Link with caps](#My-Section-Title)    ❌ Capitals not converted to lowercase
` ``

